President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his administration. John P. Pallasch of Kentucky is nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of Labor for Employment and Training. He has previous experience in the U.S. Department of Labor and the Kentucky Department of Labor. Jennifer L. Homendy of Virginia is nominated to be a Member of the National Transportation Safety Board. She currently serves as Democratic Staff Director of the Subcommittee on Railroads, Pipelines, and Hazardous Materials for the Committee on Transportation and Infrastructure. President Trump also intends to appoint Eileen Lappin Weiser of Michigan, Cardinal Donald William Wuerl of the District of Columbia, Tina S. Holland of Louisiana, and Sally Atwater of South Carolina to the Commission on Presidential Scholars.